TITLE: Converting PHPUnit Assertions - Default Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the default behavior of the php_unit_construct rule which converts generic assertion methods to their more specific alternatives. Transforms assertEquals, assertSame, assertNotEquals, and assertNotSame when used with boolean and null values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/php-cs-fixer/php-cs-fixer/blob/master/doc/rules/php_unit/php_unit_construct.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
final class FooTest extends \PHPUnit_Framework_TestCase {
    public function testSomething() {
        $this->assertEquals(false, $b);
        $this->assertSame(true, $a);
        $this->assertNotEquals(null, $c);
        $this->assertNotSame(null, $d);
    }
}
```

