TITLE: Default Configuration Example in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the default ordering of class elements including traits, constants, properties, and methods with their various visibility levels.
SOURCE: https://github.com/php-cs-fixer/php-cs-fixer/blob/master/doc/rules/class_notation/ordered_class_elements.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
final class Example
{
    use BarTrait;
    use BazTrait;
    const C1 = 1;
    const C2 = 2;
    public static $pubStatProp1;
    var $pubProp2;
    public static $pubStatProp2;
    public $pubProp3;
    protected static $protStatProp;
    protected $protProp;
    private static $privStatProp;
    private $privProp;
    protected function __construct() {}
    public function __destruct() {}
    public function __toString() {}
    public function pubFunc1() {}
    function pubFunc2() {}
    public static function pubStatFunc1() {}
    public function pubFunc3() {}
    static function pubStatFunc2() {}
    protected function protFunc() {}
    protected static function protStatFunc() {}
    private static function privStatFunc() {}
    private function privFunc() {}
}
```

