TITLE: Replacing Type Casting Functions with Operators in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how the 'modernize_types_casting' rule replaces function calls like intval(), floatval(), doubleval(), strval(), and boolval() with their corresponding type casting operators. This change improves code readability and potentially performance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/php-cs-fixer/php-cs-fixer/blob/master/doc/rules/cast_notation/modernize_types_casting.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
<?php
-    $a = intval($b);
-    $a = floatval($b);
-    $a = doubleval($b);
-    $a = strval ($b);
-    $a = boolval($b);
+    $a = (int) $b;
+    $a = (float) $b;
+    $a = (float) $b;
+    $a = (string) $b;
+    $a = (bool) $b;
```

