TITLE: Modernizing strpos calls with default configuration in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how the rule transforms strpos() calls to str_starts_with() and str_contains() with default configuration settings. The rule focuses on replacing comparison patterns like '=== 0', '!== 0', '!== false', and '=== false'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/php-cs-fixer/php-cs-fixer/blob/master/doc/rules/alias/modernize_strpos.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
--- Original
+++ New
 <?php
-if (strpos($haystack, $needle) === 0) {}
-if (strpos($haystack, $needle) !== 0) {}
-if (strpos($haystack, $needle) !== false) {}
-if (strpos($haystack, $needle) === false) {}
+if (str_starts_with($haystack, $needle)  ) {}
+if (!str_starts_with($haystack, $needle)  ) {}
+if (str_contains($haystack, $needle)  ) {}
+if (!str_contains($haystack, $needle)  ) {}
```

