TITLE: Removing Binary Prefix from Single-Quoted String (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This diff example demonstrates the `no_binary_string` rule removing the `b` prefix from a single-quoted PHP string literal. The original code `b'foo'` is transformed into `'foo'`. This ensures compatibility and consistency by avoiding the binary string notation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/php-cs-fixer/php-cs-fixer/blob/master/doc/rules/string_notation/no_binary_string.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
.. code-block:: diff

   --- Original
   +++ New
   -<?php $a = b'foo';
   +<?php $a = 'foo';
```

