TITLE: Converting FQCN strings to ::class keywords in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how the class_keyword rule transforms fully qualified class name strings into ::class syntax. It converts both single-quoted and double-quoted strings to the ::class format.
SOURCE: https://github.com/php-cs-fixer/php-cs-fixer/blob/master/doc/rules/language_construct/class_keyword.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
--- Original
+++ New
 <?php

-$foo = 'PhpCsFixer\Tokenizer\Tokens';
-$bar = "\PhpCsFixer\Tokenizer\Tokens";
+$foo = \PhpCsFixer\Tokenizer\Tokens::class;
+$bar = \PhpCsFixer\Tokenizer\Tokens::class;
```

