TITLE: Default Configuration Example - PHP Function Invocation
DESCRIPTION: Shows how the rule adds leading backslashes to function calls with default configuration settings. Focuses on array_key_exists() function call.
SOURCE: https://github.com/php-cs-fixer/php-cs-fixer/blob/master/doc/rules/function_notation/native_function_invocation.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
--- Original
+++ New
 <?php

 function baz($options)
 {
-    if (!array_key_exists("foo", $options)) {
+    if (!\array_key_exists("foo", $options)) {
         throw new \InvalidArgumentException();
     }

     return json_encode($options);
 }
```

