TITLE: Applying PhpdocToParamType Rule with Union Types Disabled in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This example illustrates the behavior of the PhpdocToParamType rule when union_types configuration is set to false. It only applies the rule to non-union types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/php-cs-fixer/php-cs-fixer/blob/master/doc/rules/function_notation/phpdoc_to_param_type.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
--- Original
+++ New
 <?php

 /** @param Foo $foo */
-function foo($foo) {}
+function foo(Foo $foo) {}
 /** @param int|string $foo */
 function bar($foo) {}
```

